sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K115031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Expression of luciferase with RNA-thermometer K115003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Expression of luciferase with a ribosome binding site repressed by thermometer K115003. An arabinose inducible promoter is used.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: O.M.J.A. Stassen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AraC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: AraC operator, truncated to include araO1, araI1, araI2, c-amp1, and c-amp2 sites. This operator should *activate* transcription in the presence of AraC; b/c the operator lacks the araO2 site, there should not be araC-mediated repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sara Neves (Fighting Darwins)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K115003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is designed as a temperature inducible RBS. Only designed so far.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: O.M.J.A. Stassen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is taken from the Listeria Monocytogenes (EU372032.). It's the 5'UTR of a TF induced at 37 degrees.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The secondary structure is important to the function of these regions, but part of the wt secondary structure is destroyed by the scar. We've tried to alter the sequence so the predicted structure (through mfold and those kind of servers) is sort of conserved, but temperature sensitivity still has to be tested. If it doesn't work, possible solution might be the addition of a larger conserved part of the wt, which implies a small part of wt protein sequence as well.

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Predicted stem loop up to A of AUG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J52008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: luciferase: luciferin 2-monooxygenase from Renilla reniformis (EC 1.13.12.5; SwissProt:: P27652)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Rluc is a protein called Renilla`s luciferase and it emits light when adding the right substrate. That is why it can bi used as a reported to track other proteins or to monitor the activity of a promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Monika Ciglic
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Rluc is cloned in BioBrick vector pSB1AK3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
